07/03/20, 10:34 pm - Sona: Hi, my name is sonali
..
Those who have known me in some way, no matter what stage of my life, surely know a little bit about me. Maybe we’re not linked anymore, but I want to believe that that’s not permanent. I’m curious to know how willing we are to use our time to write something to someone else. I decided to participate in an experiment called “a meeting with friends”. The idea is to see who reads about me in a post , as we are so immersed in the images, that any concentration on reading is appreciated. If no one reads this message, it will be a short social experience, but if you read to the end, I want you to write a word that connects you to me. For example, a place, an object, a person, a moment that brings us back to our past or current relationship. After, as the experience dictates, copy the text and paste on your wall. I’m going to your wall to leave a note that ties me to you.  Gratitude!
Don’t forget to change your name at the beginning of the text. Just as you remember, people remember you too.

09/03/20, 1:37 pm - MAYANK SINGH: Dear students, 
We are all aware that the scheduled cultural and tech fest 2020, IIT Jammu has been postponed as a precautionary measure and because of govt advisory on mass gatherings due to the ongoing coronavirus situation. It is acknowledged that a lot of you have worked tirelessly to make these fests a reality and understandably so it is discouraging and distressing after having put in tremendous efforts, time and creativity. Considering all of this, incase there is any of you who is finding it difficult to deal with the implications of postponing the fests and is struggling to come to terms with it, may please contact me at 9871910024, anytime. 

Regards,
Akankasha Joshi
Student counsellor,
IIT Jammu
